class Solution {
    public String robotWithString(String s) {
        int n = s.length();
        char[] arr = s.toCharArray();
        char[] minArr = new char[n];
        minArr[n - 1] = arr[n - 1];
        for (int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {
            minArr[i] = (char) Math.min(arr[i], minArr[i + 1]);
        }
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        java.util.Stack<Character> stack = new java.util.Stack<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            stack.push(arr[i]);
            while (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() <= minArr[i]) {
                sb.append(stack.pop());
            }
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Utilizes a stack to track characters and a min array to keep track of the minimum character from the current index to the end, allowing for efficient comparison and appending of characters to the result string in lexicographically smallest order.
